
  After forking the repository:
code {
git clone https://github.com/FORKING_USER/repo
cd repo
code }

  Add the → development/version-control-systems/git/commands/remote[remote]. Note the final `.git` in the → development/web/URI-URL-URN-IRI-URC#url[URL]:
code {
git remote add upstream https://github.com/ORIGINAL_OWNER/repo.git
git remote -v
code }

code {
→ development/version-control-systems/git/commands/fetch[git fetch] upstream
code }

  Checkout desired branch
code {
→ development/version-control-systems/git/commands/checkout[git checkout] master # or main, or xyz
code }

code {
→ development/version-control-systems/git/commands/merge[git merge] upstream/master # or main, or xyz …
code }

code {
git push
code }
